spanGrp.span: They came from a place called Valle de la Estrella.
Jeska jie-wa beteũ-te mãĩ kã' kie (_) Valle de la Estrella
From there they walked a lot in the mountain and came out from high above [the mountain].
Jeska jie-wa shká komĩ' montaña nã deu-lo jui wa
Talamanca is located on the other side;
Je wa nã esteee Talamanka jatanã jamĩwa
they walked amid bushes and paths, and so they reached Ujarras.
je wa jie-wa shkö-gẽ rö kã'yiga nã bö triyo nã bö Jeska jie-wa deu-lo jiska (_) Ujarras
the place was full of trees and bushes;
kã' rö puro kal-wa jebö kã'yiga jebö
there was nothing, no people living here.
ka jirö ta ka pe sẽr kunã
There they lived and met others and got horny and got married at once, in Ujarraz.
jeska jie-wa se-nã' jeska nẽ jie-wa ñã sũã'-nẽ kwã wa jeska nẽ jie-wa jie-wa ñã jie-wa butanã-ka tã'ĩ jie-wa ñã sũã' otro-wa ra jeska nẽ jie-wa yabla konã' jiwa jie-wa ñã jula gugá-tula-mĩ ji Ujarras
Jeska nẽ (_) yís (r) yís antepasado-wa beteũ-te Talamanka
My clan’s name is Julaglöwa; there are only two clans in Ujarraz, Julaglöwa and Kibéglöwa;
(_) yís clan rö Julablöwa y Ujarras sa clan solamente bo-tkö' bö Julaglöwa jãmẽ Kibéglöwa
my family belongs to the Julagöwa clan;
the others belong to the Kibéglöwa clan.
if they had not come here, we would be living in Talamanca, but since they came here we now live here;
jeska nẽ sa/se (_) kenãnãra ka jie-wa bötö-pa-ra sa sẽr-gẽ rö Talamanka pero komo jie-wa beteũ-lo-te jiwa je nẽ wa sa sẽr-gẽ jiwa
je nẽ wa sa sẽr-gẽ jiwa
we would not be living in Ujarraz.
kenanã ka sa sẽr kũnã Ujarras
That’s why our ancestors left us here in this other place to take care of;
je nẽ kweinga sa antepasado-wa të sa jawã'tanã ji ji ji kã' kajki kwãwa kenẽga könãna sa ka rö jiwa kunã
we live in a different place.
